  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-16"><div class="section"><div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">New York Fire Code Requirements</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">New York City enforces its own NYC Fire Code — a distinct local law that is not the International Fire Code (IFC) — through the Fire Department of New York (FDNY) Bureau of Fire Prevention. NYC's fire code is among the most comprehensive and stringent in the world, reflecting the extraordinary density of New York's commercial environment across all five boroughs. All fire protection work in New York City must be performed by contractors holding specific NYC licenses — separate from New York State licensing. The FDNY Bureau of Fire Prevention conducts tens of thousands of commercial inspections annually and is one of the most active fire code enforcement agencies in the world.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">New York City's commercial landscape spans Manhattan's iconic high-rise office and hotel corridor, Midtown's convention and entertainment district, Times Square's dense assembly occupancy zone, Brooklyn's rapidly converting industrial and creative spaces, Queens' diverse commercial and industrial operations near JFK and LaGuardia airports, the Bronx's manufacturing and food distribution facilities, and Staten Island's commercial and industrial zones. New York's extreme commercial density — with more square feet of occupied commercial space per square mile than any other US city — creates fire protection compliance obligations at extraordinary scale and complexity.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Key standards include <a href="/compliance/nfpa-10/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 10</a>, <a href="/compliance/nfpa-72/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 72</a>, and <a href="/compliance/nfpa-25/" class="text-red-brand hover:underline">NFPA 25</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">New York Fire Prevention Contacts</h3>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <div><p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-800">Fire Department of New York (FDNY) — Fire Prevention</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-600">9 MetroTech Center, Brooklyn, NY 11201</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Phone: (718) 999-2000</p></div>
          <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-3"><p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-800">NYS Office of Fire Prevention and Control (OFPC)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Licensing & Enforcement: (518) 474-6746</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
